# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: NeitherPath7
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Marion stumbles around, expecting a betrayal that never comes."
    new "Marion stumbles around, expecting a betrayal that never comes."

    old "You have until the end of next day."
    new "You have until the end of next day."

    old "After that, every soldier or peasant will be given free reign to kill you on sight, and paid handsomely if they do."
    new "After that, every soldier or peasant will be given free reign to kill you on sight, and paid handsomely if they do."

    old "Marion doesn't speak, he only turns and runs."
    new "Marion doesn't speak, he only turns and runs."

    old "Sarah would later learn that he took a remaining horse from the stables and rode out towards the border with Normandi."
    new "Sarah would later learn that he took a remaining horse from the stables and rode out towards the border with Normandi."

    old "After that, no more news came."
    new "After that, no more news came."

    old "The war had been won, and Sarah cared little for Marion anymore."
    new "The war had been won, and Sarah cared little for Marion anymore."

    old "Without his family, his base of support, his resources, he was just a man. Clever, ambitious, but just one man. Let him live out his days on the edge of the world."
    new "Without his family, his base of support, his resources, he was just a man. Clever, ambitious, but just one man. Let him live out his days on the edge of the world."

    old "Her army looted the ancestral home of the Achillea family, bringing home great coffers of gold, artifacts and relics to Castle Reinmeer."
    new "Her army looted the ancestral home of the Achillea family, bringing home great coffers of gold, artifacts and relics to Castle Reinmeer."

    old "Even with the share of the loot that dissapeared into the pockets of soldiers, the Rose family found their fortunes greatly expanded."
    new "Even with the share of the loot that dissapeared into the pockets of soldiers, the Rose family found their fortunes greatly expanded."

    old "On the road back to Castle Reinmeer, Sarah did not let Thomas go from her sight."
    new "On the road back to Castle Reinmeer, Sarah did not let Thomas go from her sight."

    old "Riding in the wagon with her, he told her of his experience in the dungeon. His hand was missing a finger which spoke enough of his trials."
    new "Riding in the wagon with her, he told her of his experience in the dungeon. His hand was missing a finger which spoke enough of his trials."

    old "Still, for as much as Thomas told Sarah, she knew her brother well enough that he was also keeping much more from her."
    new "Still, for as much as Thomas told Sarah, she knew her brother well enough that he was also keeping much more from her."

    old "At nights, on the road back home, she would find him tossing and turning in his sleep. He spoke often, screamed even."
    new "At nights, on the road back home, she would find him tossing and turning in his sleep. He spoke often, screamed even."

    old "The tortures that he had suffered had left marks on his body as well as his mind."
    new "The tortures that he had suffered had left marks on his body as well as his mind."

    old "Sarah feared only those of the body would heal any time soon."
    new "Sarah feared only those of the body would heal any time soon."

    old "Only when Sarah watched her brother step into Castle Reinmeer, did she finally feel truly safe again."
    new "Only when Sarah watched her brother step into Castle Reinmeer, did she finally feel truly safe again."

    old "In the months that followed, Sarah did her best to support her brother, but though his withered body regained its strength, he remained forever changed."
    new "In the months that followed, Sarah did her best to support her brother, but though his withered body regained its strength, he remained forever changed."

    old "Her brother survived by retreating. Retreating from the outside world, and partially even from himself."
    new "Her brother survived by retreating. Retreating from the outside world, and partially even from himself."

    old "Thomas became more like the young boy she had known her brother to be. Distant, lost in books, detached."
    new "Thomas became more like the young boy she had known her brother to be. Distant, lost in books, detached."

    old "As the burdens of rule fell evermore to Sarah, she did not complain. She would have gladly done anything to relieve him of his burdens."
    new "As the burdens of rule fell evermore to Sarah, she did not complain. She would have gladly done anything to relieve him of his burdens."

    old "In the end, it was Thomas who spoke of it first."
    new "In the end, it was Thomas who spoke of it first."

    old "Both realized the realm could not thrive with a king who was no king, and so her brother proposed that she replace him."
    new "Both realized the realm could not thrive with a king who was no king, and so her brother proposed that she replace him."

    old "Sarah never wanted the crown for herself, but she accepted the role of regent, to rule in his stead until the day he would be better, though both feared such a day would never come."
    new "Sarah never wanted the crown for herself, but she accepted the role of regent, to rule in his stead until the day he would be better, though both feared such a day would never come."

    old "Once regent, Sarah took control of her nation's government in all but name, and her brother abandoned what last few tasks he still did, dissapearing entirely into his room and the royal libraries."
    new "Once regent, Sarah took control of her nation's government in all but name, and her brother abandoned what last few tasks he still did, dissapearing entirely into his room and the royal libraries."

    old "Much damage had been caused by both the invasion of the tribesmen and the uprising of the old houses."
    new "Much damage had been caused by both the invasion of the tribesmen and the uprising of the old houses."

    old "Sarah took it upon herself to heal these wounds as best she could."
    new "Sarah took it upon herself to heal these wounds as best she could."

    old "The border provinces were reinforced, making sure that no future tribesmen army could strike at the heart of her country again."
    new "The border provinces were reinforced, making sure that no future tribesmen army could strike at the heart of her country again."

    old "The old houses were dealt with in their own way."
    new "The old houses were dealt with in their own way."

    old "Some, like the Achillea family, all but vanished from existence, their homes and properties seized, their family members hunted."
    new "Some, like the Achillea family, all but vanished from existence, their homes and properties seized, their family members hunted."

    old "For others, like the Highfield family, all those that bore the most guilt were strung from the gallows, but the smaller branches were allowed to live."
    new "For others, like the Highfield family, all those that bore the most guilt were strung from the gallows, but the smaller branches were allowed to live."

    old "Lily Highfield was promoted to head of her family, seizing control of the estate, ensuring there would always be a loyal head to one of the old houses."
    new "Lily Highfield was promoted to head of her family, seizing control of the estate, ensuring there would always be a loyal head to one of the old houses."

    old "In the end, though the old houses still existed in some fashion, their power was forever broken by Sarah, ensuring they could never rise up against her family."
    new "In the end, though the old houses still existed in some fashion, their power was forever broken by Sarah, ensuring they could never rise up against her family."

    old "Varga, her warmaster, stood by Sarah as loyal as anyone could be."
    new "Varga, her warmaster, stood by Sarah as loyal as anyone could be."

    old "He travelled on her behalf across the nation, serving as her harder hand for when her soft touch failed to convince."
    new "He travelled on her behalf across the nation, serving as her harder hand for when her soft touch failed to convince."

    old "But with Sarah's skillful guidance, her nation fell into a soft and easy peace, as had existed for many years under her father."
    new "But with Sarah's skillful guidance, her nation fell into a soft and easy peace, as had existed for many years under her father."

    old "The ravages of war were put behind them and Rosanna flourished."
    new "The ravages of war were put behind them and Rosanna flourished."

    old "With its economy back on track, the nation soon began overtaking even many of its neighbours."
    new "With its economy back on track, the nation soon began overtaking even many of its neighbours."

    old "While the old system of nobility continued to exist, new laws granted greater rights to citizens of all classes."
    new "While the old system of nobility continued to exist, new laws granted greater rights to citizens of all classes."

    old "In time, Rosanna became a destination for scholars from around the world, attracted to the freedoms offered by its government."
    new "In time, Rosanna became a destination for scholars from around the world, attracted to the freedoms offered by its government."

    old "Sarah was present when the nation's first university, the Rose University, was officially opened."
    new "Sarah was present when the nation's first university, the Rose University, was officially opened."

    old "From across the world, stories of troubles came to them, such as the fall of old Bagrad. But Rosanna was spared, becoming a safe haven in an unsafe world."
    new "From across the world, stories of troubles came to them, such as the fall of old Bagrad. But Rosanna was spared, becoming a safe haven in an unsafe world."

    old "As the peace settled and the nation gathered around its new regent, there was less and less need of Varga's more forceful hand."
    new "As the peace settled and the nation gathered around its new regent, there was less and less need of Varga's more forceful hand."

    old "And so it was that five years passed."
    new "And so it was that five years passed."

    old "Returning to Castle Reinmeer, Sarah brings her brother's body with her."
    new "Returning to Castle Reinmeer, Sarah brings her brother's body with her."

    old "She does not leave his side for the entire voyage back home."
    new "She does not leave his side for the entire voyage back home."

    old "When they arrive, the news is pronounced and the capitol enters a month of mourning, ordering all festivities and music silenced."
    new "When they arrive, the news is pronounced and the capitol enters a month of mourning, ordering all festivities and music silenced."

    old "During the funeral of her brother, when he is placed in the family grave next to her father and mother, Sarah leans on Lady Carolyn."
    new "During the funeral of her brother, when he is placed in the family grave next to her father and mother, Sarah leans on Lady Carolyn."

    old "During the funeral of her brother, when he is placed in the family grave next to her father and mother, Sarah leans on Lily."
    new "During the funeral of her brother, when he is placed in the family grave next to her father and mother, Sarah leans on Lily."

    old "During the funeral of her brother, when he is placed in the family grave next to her father and mother, Sarah stands by herself, alone."
    new "During the funeral of her brother, when he is placed in the family grave next to her father and mother, Sarah stands by herself, alone."

    old "Once queen, Sarah assumes control of her nation's government."
    new "Once queen, Sarah assumes control of her nation's government."

    old "Sarah watches as the many invited guests flow into the great hall."
    new "Sarah watches as the many invited guests flow into the great hall."

    old "The annual celebration of Rosanna's unity is underway. Officially meant to celebrate the many ways in which the nation was thriving, in truth, a reminder of how Sarah had brought low the usurpers."
    new "The annual celebration of Rosanna's unity is underway. Officially meant to celebrate the many ways in which the nation was thriving, in truth, a reminder of how Sarah had brought low the usurpers."

    old "She smiled and greeted the throng of newcomers."
    new "She smiled and greeted the throng of newcomers."

    old "On the far side of the room, Varga was chatting with a group of nobles."
    new "On the far side of the room, Varga was chatting with a group of nobles."

    old "Sarah could only laugh whenever she watched Varga try to play his part."
    new "Sarah could only laugh whenever she watched Varga try to play his part."

    old "The years had made him more talented at pretending, but she had long accepted that her warmaster would never truly be a creature of the court."
    new "The years had made him more talented at pretending, but she had long accepted that her warmaster would never truly be a creature of the court."

    old "She was happy for that fact."
    new "She was happy for that fact."

    old "The crowd had changed over the years."
    new "The crowd had changed over the years."

    old "Nobles still made up a large share of those in attendance, but each passing year the crowd grew more diverse. Sucessful merchants, famous scholars, notable guests from across the world."
    new "Nobles still made up a large share of those in attendance, but each passing year the crowd grew more diverse. Sucessful merchants, famous scholars, notable guests from across the world."

    old "Rosanna had become somewhat of a hub for all those who sought to make their luck for themselves."
    new "Rosanna had become somewhat of a hub for all those who sought to make their luck for themselves."

    old "Sarah was glad for it, if only because the new crowd seemed less obsessed with protocol."
    new "Sarah was glad for it, if only because the new crowd seemed less obsessed with protocol."

    old "Still, no royal court could ever truly escape it, and so Sarah continued to play her part."
    new "Still, no royal court could ever truly escape it, and so Sarah continued to play her part."

    old "Each guest bore with them a gift, and soon the many gifts began to pile up next to her. The pile grew so large that it soon became embarassing."
    new "Each guest bore with them a gift, and soon the many gifts began to pile up next to her. The pile grew so large that it soon became embarassing."

    old "With a small gesture of a hand, Sarah instructed the servants to begin carrying the gifts away for storage."
    new "With a small gesture of a hand, Sarah instructed the servants to begin carrying the gifts away for storage."

